                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cgmartin",
                        "name": "cgmartin",
                        "displayName": "Chris Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The FormLabel's translation functionality is covered with a unit test (and currently passing):\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/blob\/master\/tests\/ZendTest\/Form\/View\/Helper\/FormLabelTest.php#L145-L160\r\n\r\nFor the translator to automatically attach to the view helpers, the translator should be in the service locator. Example via config from the skeleton application:\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/ZendSkeletonApplication\/blob\/master\/module\/Application\/config\/module.config.php#L60-L69\r\n\r\nHere is the code that pulls it out of the service locator and attaches it to the view helpers (including FormLabel):\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/blob\/master\/library\/Zend\/View\/HelperPluginManager.php#L136-L144\r\n\r\nSome things to check:\r\n * Confirm that the translator is set on the FormLabel helper: var_dump($this->formLabel()->getTranslator())\r\n * Do the translation text domains match?: var_dump($this->formLabel()->getTranslatorTextDomain())\r\n * Does the translation key match and exist in your DE translation file?\r\n\r\n\r\nEDIT: Apologies, I just noticed your output of both FormRow and FormLabel together... I will set up a test here and take a look see. Thanks!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cgmartin",
                        "name": "cgmartin",
                        "displayName": "Chris Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-09-05T22:44:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-09-05T22:47:39.000+0000"
                },
